Class Medication

  • java.lang.Object
    • Medication

  • public class Medication
extends java.lang.Object
    Medication is a class representing a single medication, identified by its generic name and current dispensing dosage.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Medication other)
        Two medications are equivalent if they have the same generic name and equal dosages.
        Parameters:
        other - The medication that may or may not be equivalent to this medication.
        Returns:
        True if this medication is equivalent to other, false otherwise.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Medication other)
        Determines the ordering of two medications. Ordering is determined by the alphabetical ordering of the name followed by the numerical ordering of the dosage.
        Parameters:
        other - The medication to compare to this medication.
        Returns:
        n, where n is either:
        • 0 if the medications are equivalent,
        • < 0 if this medication precedes the other medication, or
        • > 0 if this medication comes after the other mediation.
